{"id":"9166","name":"Notionminder","tagline":"Runs a script that will update a Beeminder goal with the total word count in a notion database.","icon":"ios14 c4274264319 g59798","latest":"27415","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Intended to be used along with a Scriptable script found here: https://github.com/travisbostick/notionminder/blob/main/Scriptable/notionminder_scriptable.js</p>\n<p>This shortcut triggers the script that will count the words in a notion database. It will then send that word count to a Beeminder goal to update and track the total.</p>\n<p>To use, insert the following values in the dictionary:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The ID of the Notion database you want to track.</li>\n<li>Your Notion API Key (Internal Integration Token)</li>\n<li>Your Beeminder auth_token</li>\n<li>The name of the Beeminder goal you want to update</li>\n<li>Your Beeminder username</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Make sure to select the correct Scriptable script in the shortcut.</p>\n<p>Instructions to find this information can be found here: https://developers.notion.com/docs/getting-started</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - May 15, 2021, 6:25 p.m.</strong></p>"}